Given the magnitude of what we're up against, I see no harm in considering the benefit this offer might afford us. It could be the only way to reach this 'source' in one piece.
Is it me, or is the ground here particularly sticky? Almost as if...

EditorData.logicalname: 62 - You are in the bhaal domain of the sewers

Text.Value: Glad to see I'm not the only one on the wrong side of an omnipotent authority figure.

EditorData.logicalname: 141 - Vlaakith appeared in camp as a hologram and Lae'zel was on Orpheus path after

Text.Value: Not sure now is the time for chatter. There's a raging inferno surrounding us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coughing slightly - in the vicinity of a burning building, though not necessarily inside it

Text.Value: Of course. Sometimes I forget who I'm travelling with. It takes some getting used to, walking amongst peers again.
Remember his Cormyrian rhyme? 'Down came the claw'. Perhaps we should start growing our nails.
An admirable choice, if not one that will make achieving our purpose any easier.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not overly concerned by the choice, wouldn't have minded Astarion wielding the vampire lord's powers

Text.Value: Our tadpoles are part of the problem, not a solution. We shouldn't rely on them or their powers.
I'll gladly talk to you about such matters when the time comes. But for now, let's speak of other things.
But you don't need me to tell you this. You're here about something else, I'll wager?
If there's one quality all the denizens of the Hells embody, it's ambition. A quality they share with many humans, come to think of it...
No amount of contracts will save Raphael from the fate we forced upon him. A devil well-slain, if I say so myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight

Text.Value: This Orphic Hammer sounds like quite the artefact. One I'll have no desire to consume, if that's your concern.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight

Text.Value: Replete with ribaldry, as always. Well, you could provide no better proof that you are not, in fact, about to turn into a mind flayer.
Aha. What an interesting question...

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly uncomfortable. Been asked if he could use a potentially evil kind of magic, if he wanted to...

Text.Value: I hope your confidence proves well-founded. God knows we could use all the help we can get.
But what is it that this devil wants so very badly?
Followers of Mystra - those who call on the true Weave - are expressly forbidden to indulge it.
Whatever ancient purpose is imbued in these halls, it may not welcome our presence here. We should be wary of whatever lurks beneath the dust.
I've never had cause to visit a druid's grove before. Magic weighs heavier here, seeking solace in root and soil. Grounding, one might say.
Glad to see we all made it through the night intact. A promising sign that we may be able to curb those urges of yours.

EditorData.NodeContext: Concerned

Text.Value: Hmm. I suspect we define the word differently, but nonetheless - this is a place where it's best applied. This magic is dangerous.
Famously humourless, illithids. The tyrannical enslavement of all other living creatures hardly lends itself to levity. Should your wit begin to suffer, only then must we worry.
Whatever that thing was you turned into, I'd rather not see it again. By the gods...

EditorData.NodeContext: Disturbed, in shock

Text.Value: You don't believe this was a real person talking to you then?
The living may not be prevented from crossing a vampire's threshold, but that doesn't make us any more welcome. Tread carefully.

EditorData.logicalname: 58 - You are heading in Cazador's dungeon

Text.Value: I feel the Weave growing more distant by the moment. We walk Shar's path now - best we don't spend too long in her shadow.

EditorData.logicalname: 39 - You are in the shar temple

Text.Value: The world is full of oddities, but even so, that was... unexpected.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coverage - generic greeting reacting to recent situation. Slightly baffled.

EditorData.logicalname: 138 - Wyll chose to save his father and pact himself eternally to Mizora and Zariel

Text.Value: What do you think Raphael's 'ambition' could be?
Whoever inflicted the shadows on this land was no ordinary spellcaster. And certainly had no fear of Mystra's punishment for doing so.
This 'source' she referred to and the 'Heart of the Absolute' might be one and the same.
Shadow magic isn't Mystra's to claim, it might be said...
I know well the pain of seeing your life's hourglass running empty, grasping at any means of slowing the grains as they slip inexorably through your fingers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere, a note of pity - Gale once thought he was fated to die because of th orb, so her truly understands what she's going through
EditorData.logicalname: 70 - Karlach got her second upgrade and can touch people again, but dammon said he can't fix her engine and it will likely blow soon.

Text.Value: Your siblings could use a dose of your cynicism. Anyone cruel enough to pursue such a means to power has no intention of sharing it.

EditorData.logicalname: 80 - Raphael didn't tell Astarion about the ritual, but the vampire spawn at the Flophouse did.

Text.Value: A valid point. But I think it's safe to assume that were the boot on the other foot, they'd have few regrets. Ruthlessness cuts both ways. And crushes too.
So, a vampire lord walks among us. A powerful ally to have at our side, and a powerful enemy should our intentions diverge.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impressed, finding this all very interesting
EditorData.logicalname: 122 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador and became a vampire lord.

Text.Value: Best to ignore. Probably just something you ate.
Of course not. It was a dream, nothing more.
I sense the difference in you already. You seem sharper, leaner, hungrier.
A new kind of being walks among us. One with teeth.

EditorData.logicalname: 83 - Avatar Astarion faced Cazador and became a vampire lord.

Text.Value: The Astral Plane. Mortals such as we are not meant for this place. We must tread carefully.
Still, we must flow with the current we find ourselves in, however tumultuous it may be. If you've need of me, I'm glad to help.
Time for us to take a rather literal 'leap of faith'.

EditorData.logicalname: 42 - You defeated Ketheric Thorm for the first time

Text.Value: Shar may punish you, but she does not have claim on you any longer. Resisting her is a triumph in itself, however much it hurts.
Poor Shadowheart. The gods are nothing if not vindictive in their vengeance.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sympathetic - Gale also feels the gods have punished him
EditorData.logicalname: 161 - Shar punished SH after sparing NS

Text.Value: Shar's domain is a far cry from Mystra's. The Weave's light is truly extinguished by such darkness.
I'm not sure. Such an apparition has its own motives, whatever it told us.
You're familiar with devilry then?

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (122 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador and became a vampire lord.)

Text.Value: Still - don't let his bluster fool you. All that talk of desperation? It merely illustrates his own.
The Gur are certainly efficient. Astarion's fate will not be an easy one. Nor painless.
We should inform her of his delusions. No doubt she'll have great fun dispelling them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost amused by the thought, a bit of schadenfreude at his peer's idiocy

Text.Value: His intelligence may yet prove the key to unlocking the artefact's secrets. We should ensure we follow up when we reach Baldur's Gate.
What a thrill, to wander the corridors of the forge of tyranny itself. Better keep our thoughts to ourselves - who knows what might be listening to us here?

EditorData.logicalname: 56 - You are in the steel watch

Text.Value: An ally fresh from the Hells themselves. Our company grows stranger by the minute - and all the better for it.
Whether she spoke the truth or not... Well, I think I require a litle more evidence before taking a fantasy at her word.
Still, such conflicts will not serve our party well in resolving this little parasite problem of ours. Best we cast from the same spell book from now on.
Nothing wrong with maintaining a healthy suspicion in such matters.
'The Blade of Frontiers. A fitting title for one so steeled with purpose.

EditorData.NodeContext: tongue in cheek regarding Wyll's heroic moniker

Text.Value: I commend you on your willingness to take such a risk. Now, let's hope your new, illithid-fuelled prowess tip the balance suitably  in our favour.
It is the very antithesis of all the Weave stands for, a magic of confusion and corruption, drawn forth only by those desperate or damned enough to accept its degradations.
Come now. Of all people I'd think you'd see through his bluster.
That's one scourge eliminated. A vampire with that much power would be a death sentence for this city. A pity Astarion didn't understand that. Or rather, didn't care.

EditorData.logicalname: 84 - Betrayed Vampire Lord Astarion to the Gur

Text.Value: I suspect any child of Jaheira's will share her self-destructive sense of justice, but at least her words give them pause for thought.
Of all the places I expected we'd find this Minsc, crawling from the broken jaws of a mimic wasn't high on my list. What's life without a few surprises, eh?
Well that was memorable, wasn't it?

EditorData.NodeContext: Coverage - generic greeting reacting to recent situation. Neutral.

Text.Value: What's so different about shadow magic?
Didn't you use this magic to create the shadow lantern?
You aren't here to hear me ramble. What do need of me?

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral bridging nodes for coverage

Text.Value: We cannot afford to lose focus now. Not when the brain is so close. We press on.

EditorData.NodeContext: Urgent, decisive - this isn't the time for chit chat
EditorData.logicalname: 63 - You are on your way to the morphic pool

Text.Value: Let me play the devil's advocate: the man is too eager. Do not dismiss his offer out of hand.
A pity Shadowheart was the price of it, but the 'Lady of Loss' will take her dues. Our loss is our gain, so to speak.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, knows Shadowheart has a miserable life head. Last bit a play on 'their loss is our gain', as the player lost Shadowheart to gain the Shar temple's support

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (120 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador, but stayed a vampire spawn.)

Text.Value: And how do you propose we beat a devil at his own game?
Lae'zel had the makings of a formidable ally, if one prone to acts of impulsive violence.

EditorData.logicalname: 74 - Lae'zel and Shadowheart fought (both companions - Lae'zel died)

Text.Value: I suppose you're right - we still see only a part of the picture, however much our visitor claims to show the full vista of options at our disposal.
Your head must be spinning, to learn such a truth. Dame Aylin's revelations can't have been easy to stomach, but know that you will not be alone, when the time comes to act upon them.
At least Shadowheart is armed with the truth now. May its keen edge draw forth whatever vengeance she desires.

EditorData.logicalname: 162 - Shadowheart learned the truth about her past from Nightsong

Text.Value: Whatever these dark powers of yours may be, they serve no purpose if you cannot control them. Or yourself. What a terrible waste.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed at the player - they've done something terrible, and dangerous

Text.Value: This magic is the very antithesis of all the Weave stands for, a magic of confusion and corruption, drawn forth only by those desperate or damned enough to accept its degradations.
What's done is done, and what remains to be done allows no great periods of introspection on such matters. Unless there's something else to discuss, we should press on.
A fascinating structure. Made of living flesh, or merely a simulacrum?

EditorData.NodeContext: Indulging his intellectual curiosity
EditorData.logicalname: 38 You fell into the colony prison shaft

Text.Value: Having a devil in our camp will certainly make things interesting. Never a dull day, is there?

EditorData.NodeContext: Mildly amused/curious what this turn of events will bring

Text.Value: What would it do to me?
Let's hope Shadowheart's actions do not return to haunt her. I know they would haunt me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim/shocked - can't quite believe Shadoheart stooped to murdering her own parents.

Text.Value: Halsin does not deserve to die on such a craven's altar.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, this is a serious problem - referring to Halsin being abducted by Orin

Text.Value: Thank goodness that's over.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coverage - generic greeting reacting to recent situation. Neutral/ small relief.

Text.Value: That was truly remarkable...

EditorData.NodeContext: Coverage - generic greeting reacting to recent situation. Hint of awe.

Text.Value: A natural impulse to try and shield one's loved ones from danger, especially when you feel a moral compunction to run head-first towards it.

EditorData.logicalname: 89 - Speaking to Jaheira's family in Lower City

Text.Value: All this time, we were protected by a mind flayer... that is a turn up for the books.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not sure what to make of this new information
EditorData.logicalname: 46 - You are in the Astral Plane during intermezzo - after meeting Emperor

Text.Value: A shame it's so dank and decayed down here - I suspect there's a wealth of history to be uncovered, if any could hold their breath long enough to find it.
Sorry - I didn't ask why you sought me out. Do you need anything of me?

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising he's not asked why you came over, waking from his gloomy thoughts

Text.Value: At last, we find a beacon of light amongst the darkness. And not a moment too soon - I'm quite ready for some respite.
Are you still bound by Mystra's doctrine?
We should consider Orin's terms carefully, however distasteful we may find them.
Don't worry, I've no interest in prizing that artefact from your grip. Your secrets are yours to keep.

EditorData.NodeContext: A blunt observation, but with a hint of sympathy
EditorData.logicalname: 118 - Lae'zel and Shadowheart fought (SH avatar - peaceful outcome)

Text.Value: This is the seat of the Absolute's power. Whatever the 'Heart' is, it's connected to this place somehow. We must find out.
Shadowed in name, but no longer in spirit. It suits you.
Shadowed in name, but no longer in spirit. It suits her.

EditorData.NodeContext: pleased for his friend

Text.Value: What joy, to have found the nadir of common decency. Let's conclude our business here quickly, and never speak of it again.
Hunting one devil, allying yourself with another. Our journey gets more curious by the second.
A real manifestation, perhaps. But not an individual of flesh and blood in the manner you or I would consider to be 'real.'
Quite the rug pull, eh? A mind flayer manipulating us this whole time.

EditorData.logicalname: 172 - Had the reveal that the Emperor is a mind flayer in Intermezzo

Text.Value: She deserves more time to enjoy her victory. Still, there's solace to be found in surrendering one's mortality in a blaze of glory. Or so I hear.

EditorData.NodeContext: Saddened, but trying to find a positive. Continuing the dark humour in alluding to the orb, and the fact he may yet go out in his own blaze of glory

Text.Value: So, this is the seat of the Absolute's power? Every bit as vile as the cultists who flock here, by the looks of it.
Another day, another god trying to make us her playthings. We'll have the whole pantheon interfering with us if we're not careful.

EditorData.logicalname: 75 - Learned why Sharrans stole the Orpheus Box

Text.Value: Gods, I hate spiders.
At last, we stand on the cusp of victory. A narrower precipice than I hoped, but it's our destiny to traverse it nonetheless.

EditorData.NodeContext: Focused, determined
EditorData.logicalname: 64 - You arrived in the end game

Text.Value: If there's heroism to be found in politics, I'm sure you'll find it. Somewhere...
If there's heroism to be found in politics, I'm sure Wyll will find it. Somewhere...

EditorData.NodeContext: Not that impressed by Wyll's decision, doesn't think politics is a particularly noble thing to aspire to
EditorData.logicalname: 136 - Wyll is now officially going to pursue being Grand Duke in final decision

Text.Value: At best, an ally whose motivations remain shrouded in deceit. We should be wary of what such an alliance may cost us.
We'll speak more on this later, but suffice it to say for now - that crown is vital to our purpose here.
You should try to get some rest. Hard to save the world if you're stifling yawns.
I can't believe you signed that contract. We'll discuss this. Later.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight
EditorData.logicalname: 146 -  Signed the deal with Raphael in SC

Text.Value: Devils rarely approach mortals without some nefarious intent. We'd be wise to avoid him.
Astarion's fate depends on us. Given our resounding failure to protect him in the first place, I'm not sure I fancy his chances.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight

Text.Value: Could you use it yourself?
Wonderful. Advantages are a more precious commodity than I'd have hoped, given the nature of our predicament.
You're here on a different matter, I suspect?

EditorData.NodeContext: Neutral bridging nodes for coverage

Text.Value: I've known a few warlocks in my time. Talented, of course, though sometimes too eager to listen to the devils on their shoulders. Comes with the territory, unfortunately.
Time and again, your plight reinforces my decision not to pursue the path of a warlock.
Time and again, Wyll's plight reinforces my decision not to pursue the path of a warlock.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, a hint of pity
EditorData.logicalname: 137 - Wyll chose to sacrifice his father so he could get out of his pact

Text.Value: Nothing like the stench of human effluence to make you regret any and all prior life decisions.
The tadpoles, the Absolute... it was because of you? I think you've said and done more than enough. Leave me be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Really pissed off, not ready to talk about it. Learned the DU was an originator of the Absolute plot
EditorData.logicalname: 98 - DU is chosen of Bhaal and former leader of absolute cult - revealed in Gortash ceremony

Text.Value: Fascinating as our surroundings are, we must press on. If our runaway general is down here, the Heart of the Absolute will be too.
She told me she was watching over me, protecting me. And, that our tadpoles could prove beneficial, if we embrace what powers they have to offer.
We must reach Ketheric. He will lead us to the Heart of the Absolute.
Even feigning a mortal form it was easy to detect the whiff of sulphur about him, to spot the flicker of hellfire in his eyes.

I've no wish to cast any aspersions on our existing skill set, of course, but given the perilous direction in which our journey is headed, the tadpole's powers might be a welcome addition to our arsenal.
Hardly the noblest conflict we've encountered, but criminals will have their squabbles, even in the looming shadow of utter annihilation.
Quite something, to have devotees of the Shar herself sworn to our cause.

EditorData.NodeContext: Curious at this turn of events, should sound neutral as Gale isn't necessarily a fan of Shar
EditorData.logicalname: 111 - Shadowheart got sold out by party to Viconia

Text.Value: Speaking of which, I assume you came with some other subject on your mind?
Jaheira made her choice, however unwise it may be to divide our efforts at this juncture. A shame, but we'll forge ahead without her.
You did a good thing back there. I won't dwell on the matter - I know that's not a sentiment you're accustomed to revelling in, but rest assured - your actions have spoken for themselves.

EditorData.NodeContext: A blunt observation, but with a hint of sympathy
EditorData.logicalname: 120 - Companion Astarion faced Cazador, but stayed a vampire spawn.

Text.Value: For your sake, I hope they are secrets worth their price. I wouldn't care to have Shar's wrath at my back.
Whatever they are, Shadowheart will pay dearly for them. Shar will make sure of it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bleak observation - Gale knows enough about Shadowheart's goddess, Shar, to know she will suffer for her disobedience

Text.Value: I think he wants something from us. Badly. And in that knowledge lies our opportunity.
A savvy move, recruiting Halsin to our cause.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight

Text.Value: I've never met a devil, but of course I've read a great deal about them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wants to impress upon you that his opinion is to be trusted

Text.Value: Or perhaps, a certain parasite that's clamped its jaws into me. Regardless, you're right. Better to stay focused on the real world's problems, than the fantasy of an easy solution.
This is our fault. We should've left that weapon alone.
The hammer we claimed is of incredible arcane craftsmanship. No wonder it was so fiercely protected. In the wrong hands, who knows what it might shatter...

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight

Text.Value: I hope you're still in one piece after that little reunion. Take it from me - your taste in company has much improved, if those spawn were anything to go by. Good riddance to them.
Not the kind of excitement I usually enjoy being woken up for. Still, better than not waking up at all. Or waking up as something else entirely.

EditorData.logicalname: 81 - Vampire spawn attacked the camp during the night.

Text.Value: A disturbed and disturbing night for all of us, but worth it. With due diligence, your impulses will soon be mastered. Or at least, prevented from causing further harm.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shaken, but determined - the DU's impulse was to kill him the night before. Likely a romance partner/close friend of the DU, so seeking to reassure.

Text.Value: An uncanny apparition. I'm not entirely sure what to make of it.
Revenge is a dish best served hot, it seems. At least when Karlach is in charge of the menu.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dark humour - your friend achieved her goal, but you know she'll not live long enough to celebrate
EditorData.logicalname: 71 - Karlach finished her monologue after Gortash's death, where it became clear she's going to die (Avatar)

Text.Value: The underdark has a certain menacing beauty to it. Though I'd be happier admiring it from a safe distance.
Over far too soon. I was rather enjoying that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coverage - generic greeting reacting to recent situation. Wistful.

Text.Value: Devils aren't known to aid mortals out of simple kindness. Whatever Raphael wants, we must be the key to getting it. Along with our tadpoles...

EditorData.NodeContext: Confident theorising

Text.Value: A valid point. As survival strategies go, raising your young in a building rigged to self-destruct is a rather poor one. No doubt they'd have found that out for themselves eventually.
I can't deny my curiosity, but as you say - no harm in delaying it, for now at least.
Yours was an escape narrow enough to defy even the tiniest of measuring sticks. Best to apply a touch more caution when agreeing to ambiguous medical procedures in future.
Minsc seems quite the, er, enthusiastic ally. We'd all do well to remain on his good side. And out of range of his fists.
Civilisation beckons at last. It's no Waterdeep, but Baldur's Gate is a respectable runner-up. Or at least a close third.
I've not felt the presence of the Shadow Weave like this since we left behind that cursed darkness. We must be on our guard.

EditorData.logicalname: 59 - You are in the Shar Cloister

Text.Value: They deserved to die on the battlefield, serving Vlaakith, bloodied swords in hand. We denied them that honour.
Mystra's domain is the Weave, and the magic that courses through it.
Bested by simple vampire spawn, our companion snatched like a rattle from a babe.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed, taking this as a personal slight
EditorData.logicalname: 143 - Vampire spawn attacked the camp during the night.

Text.Value: I think a quick death is the best one could hope for.
I thought Mystra was the god of all magic. Why forbid this?
Do you feel as flattered as I do? Invited to dine with a devil...
After all he'd been through... Zevlor did not deserve such a death.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to discovering Zevlor brutally murdered in camp by Orin. Slightly stunned by it

Text.Value: Now, I think it's time we moved on to lighter subjects, before we too are lost to the darkness. Was there anything else?
I'll remind you that when dealing with a devil, you always draw the short straw.
Haven't the foggiest. But based on the evidence before us, we can make certain deductions as to why he sought out our merry band.
Thank goodness that's all dealt with. The odds are stacked high enough against us already. No need to turn on each other.
So I say for now - we wait. If I'm right, Raphael will seek us out again. And when he does, there's a mighty bargain to be made.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confident theorising

Text.Value: Even being in the presence of that amulet makes my skin crawl. It's like feeling the eyes of Bhaal himself settling upon us.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a shudder - just got a gross murderer amulet

Text.Value: I'll say one thing for our troupe - we're not short on drama. I'm glad Shadowheart and Lae'zel settled their differences peacefully. Eventually.

EditorData.logicalname: 128 - Lae'zel and Shadowheart fought (Companions - peaceful outcome)

Text.Value: Any opportunities for us to indulge our tadpole's capabilities are hardly on the same scale. Trifles, when one considers the bigger picture.
Some thoughts are best left unfinished. Now, please tell me there's some other subject you wish to occupy my mind with?
I hope your business with me isn't so contentious. I much prefer to settle matters with debate, not daggers.

EditorData.NodeContext: A blunt observation, but with a hint of sympathy
EditorData.logicalname: 119 - Lae'zel and Shadowheart fought (LZ avatar - peaceful outcome)

Text.Value: A crying shame, to see such a curious piece of githyanki engineering reduced to junk parts. Still, at least it wasn't you who ended up on the scrap heap.

EditorData.logicalname: 176 - Companion witnessed avatar using Zaith'isk in Creche

Text.Value: We have our orders, from the queen of the githyanki herself, no less. Now might be the time to consider obeying them.
We have our orders, from your queen herself, no less. Now might be the time to consider obeying them.
